William Doty (gybrwe@crl.com) wrote:
: >Also, the sysop mentioned that it was for legal reasons he was
: >doing it..can this be true?  What kind of legal consequences could he be
: >getting from people using PGP on his board?  Please respond, ASAP..

: It would be my guess that the sysop does not want to encourage the use of 
: encryption on his board, or on a network that he is part of.  Basically, 
: some sysops (I've seen this for WWIVnet and FIDOnet) feel that they do 
: not want anything on their system that might be illegal.  You can encrypt 
: anything (plans to kill the president, pornography, NPD software..etc.) 
: and put it anywhere without being detected.  Since the Sysop is 
: responsible for everything on his board, legally speaking (if there is 
: illegal software/child porn etc...), then he obviously feels that he is 
: at risk by allowing or propagating PGP on his board...

: Bill

It may also have been that the sysop was worried about RSADSI coming after
him for a patent infringement (unlikely to actually happen, but still
_possible_).

Dave Merriman
